@MLStreetTalk There will always be people who want to understand stuff. I, for example, feel unhappy when I don't understand something, so I keep digging until I crack it or prove to myself that I am too dumb for this specific problem.

The problem is that even the folks who have this deep expertise now (we haven't yet all become retards as you predicted, but you might be right that it will happen at some point) cannot build anything comparable in magnitude to PayPal, Netflix, iPhone, Google Search, Facebook, Google Maps, Gmail, Amazon, AWS, AirBnB, or Uber. And all these businesses happened basically all at the same time, give or take a couple of years.

Look at what's landscape now: OpenAI invented the chatbot, and now we have: Anthropic copied the chatbot, Google copied the chatbot, xAI copied the chatbot, Chinese copied the chatbot, everyone is trying to build a fucking chatbot.

